"(1) (i) A deafening roar echoed through the dense foliage as the ground beneath Mila’s feet suddenly gave way, sending a shiver of terror down her spine. Trees snapped like twigs, and a cloud of dust and mud surged forward, swallowing the narrow road she had been walking along. The air filled with the sharp, acrid scent of wet earth, and the ground trembled again, each quake making her heart race faster. In that instant, the world she knew vanished beneath a relentless tide of debris. witnessed a landslide disaster.\n(2) (ii) Mila stumbled backward, her boots slipping on the slick, slurry surface as boulders the size of cars tumbled past with a thunderous crash. She could barely make out the outline of her friends ahead, their shouts cut short by the rumbling chaos. Debris rained down around her, some pieces landing mere inches from her face, while the distant sounds of panicked voices and sirens were drowned out by the relentless roar of the landslide. Her breath came in shallow gasps, her mind struggling to process the scale of destruction unfolding all around her.\n(3) (i) In the heart of the on , bore witness to the catastrophic landslide that swept through the mountainous path behind her village. The landslide, triggered by heavy rainfall, transformed the once-stable slopes into a torrent of earth and rock, reshaping the landscape in a matter of minutes. As the dust settled, Mila’s horror turned to a silent vow to remember and to help those lost in the face of such natural fury. Luzon Region. March 23, 2024. Mila Gonzalez."